'''Gonzalo Jordy Plata Jiménez''' (born 1 November 2000) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|right winger]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Serie A]] club [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sporting.pt/pt/futebol/equipa-principal/plantel/gonzalo-jordy-plata-jimenez|title=Gonzalo Plata|publisher=[[Sporting CP]]|language=pt|accessdate=26 August 2019|archive-date=19 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819163942/https://www.sporting.pt/pt/futebol/equipa-principal/plantel/gonzalo-jordy-plata-jimenez|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Sporting===
Plata joined [[Sporting CP|Sporting]] from Ecuadorean club [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] for an undisclosed fee during the [[2018–19 Sporting CP season|2018–19]] winter transfer window. Plata scored his first [[Primeira Liga]] goal for Sporting in a 2–0 win over [[Boavista F.C.|Boavista]] on 23 February 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20192020/liganos/22/2|title=Sporting CP 2:0 Boavista FC|website=Liga Portugal|date=23 February 2020|accessdate=21 May 2021|language=PT|archive-date=21 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210521191453/https://www.ligaportugal.pt/pt/liga/jogo/20192020/liganos/22/2|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 19 May 2021, Plata scored in Sporting's 5–1 win over [[C.S. Marítimo|Marítimo]] as the club won their first [[2020–21 Primeira Liga|Primeira Liga]] title in 19 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://primetimezone.com/sports/sporting-5-1-maritimo-pot-of-gold-to-close-the-season-zap/|title=Sporting 5-1 Marítimo: Pot of gold to close the season|website=Primetime Zone|date=20 May 2021|accessdate=21 May 2021|archive-date=21 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210521185538/https://primetimezone.com/sports/sporting-5-1-maritimo-pot-of-gold-to-close-the-season-zap/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=PL />

===Valladolid===
On 31 August 2021, Plata joined Spanish [[Segunda División]] side [[Real Valladolid]] on loan for the [[2021–22 Segunda División|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.realvalladolid.es/noticia/gonzalo-plata-potencia-el-ataque|title=Gonzalo Plata potencia el ataque|trans-title=Gonzalo Plata bolsters the attack|publisher=Real Valladolid|language=es|date=31 August 2021|accessdate=31 August 2021|archive-date=31 August 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210831221857/https://www.realvalladolid.es/noticia/gonzalo-plata-potencia-el-ataque|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 July 2022, Plata was purchased by Valladolid, signing a contract until 2027.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.abola.pt/Nnh/Noticias/Ver/948881 | title=Oficial: Plata em definitivo no Valladolid (Espanha) | access-date=11 July 2022 | archive-date=11 July 2022 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220711114226/https://www.abola.pt/Nnh/Noticias/Ver/948881 | url-status=live }}</ref>

===Al Sadd===
On 23 July 2023, Plata joined [[Qatar Stars League]] side [[Al Sadd SC|Al Sadd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/AlsaddSC/status/1683221044176273409|title=OFFICIAL: Gonzalo Plata signs for #AlSadd on a five-year deal starting from the 2023-24 season|publisher=Twitter|language=en|date=23 July 2023|accessdate=23 July 2023|archive-date=24 July 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230724001436/https://twitter.com/AlsaddSC/status/1683221044176273409|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Flamengo===
On 30 August 2024, Plata joined Brazilian side [[CR Flamengo|Flamengo]].<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.flamengo.com.br/noticias/futebol/gonzalo-plata-e-o-mais-novo-reforco-do-mengao|title=Gonzalo Plata é o mais novo reforço do Mengão|trans-title=Gonzalo Plata is Mengão’s newest reinforcement|language=pt|date=30 August 2024|website=CR Flamengo}}</ref>

He scored the goal that secured the [[2024 Copa do Brasil]] 5th trophy for Flamengo by winning 1-0 against [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] at [[Arena MRV]].

==International career==

Plata was selected in the 28 player Ecuador squad for the [[2021 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Ecuadorian Football Federation]]|user=LaTri|number=1402825519754797058|title=¡Y los convocados son! Estos son los elegidos por el DT #GustavoAlfaro para encarar un desafío continental: la @CopaAmerica.|date=9 June 2021|access-date=9 June 2021|language=es}}</ref>

Plata was named in the Ecuadorian squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Ecuador national football team |author-link=Ecuador national football team |user=LaTri |number=1592288685797494784 |date=14 November 2022 |title=Aquí están los 26 jugadores elegidos por el DT Gustavo Alfaro para jugar la Copa Mundial FIFA, estamos listos para hacer historia |trans-title=Here are the 26 players chosen by head coach Gustavo Alfaro to play the FIFA World Cup, we are ready to make history. |language=es |access-date=14 November 2022}}</ref>

